  "prompt": "Does India contribute to the ISS (International Space Station)?",
  "response": "As of now, India is not a partner in the International Space Station (ISS) program. The primary countries involved in the ISS are the United States, Russia, Japan, Canada, and member states of the European Space Agency (ESA). However, India, through its space agency ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation), has been actively engaging in other international space collaborations and has growing ambitions in space exploration, including plans for its own space station in the future.",
